OL,3,CBank of England must better address
OL,4,Cclimate risk to tackle inflation, WWF
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThis is because the UK imports a
OL,8,Fsignificant amount of its fruit,
OL,9,Fvegetables, meat and fish, with
OL,10,Fextreme weather events abroad
OL,11,Faffecting supply chains.
OL,13,FCoffee and cocoa are among the
OL,14,Fcommodities to have seen surging
OL,15,Fprices in recent years as climate
OL,16,Fconditions become increasingly
OL,17,Fvolatile in areas of the world where
OL,18,Fthese crops can be grown.
OL,20,FThe Bank of England has been
OL,21,Fapproached for comment.
